# Godot ↔ Cursor / VS Code

## Project folder on disk (no spaces)

Prefer the project directory name **`StoneAgeClans`** so Windows shells never split `--path`. If the folder is still **`Stone Age Clans`**, close Cursor and Godot, then run **`tools/rename_this_folder_to_StoneAgeClans.ps1`** (or `stoneageclans/rename_project_folder.ps1` if you use the parent wrapper layout).

## `godotTools.editorPath.godot4` (workspace `.vscode/settings.json`)

- Use a path **relative to the project root**, e.g. `tools/godot/Godot_v4.6.1-stable_win64.exe`.
- **Do not** put `${workspaceFolder}` in that value. The godot-tools extension already resolves paths from the workspace root; a literal `${workspaceFolder}` segment produces an invalid path and breaks the LSP / “open editor”.
- **`${workspaceFolder}` is correct** in `.vscode/launch.json` and `.vscode/tasks.json` — VS Code expands those; the bug is specific to **godot-tools `editorPath` settings**.

## `tools/godot/godot.cmd`

- Must delegate to exes next to the script via `%~dp0` (or equivalent). **Never** commit hardcoded `C:\Users\...` paths.
- Prefer console build when present; fall back to the standard GUI build (see `tools/godot/README.txt`).

## Before merging `.vscode` or `godot.cmd` changes

Run the VS Code task **`Godot: Verify Cursor/VS Code setup`**, or:

`powershell -NoProfile -File tools/verify_vscode_godot_setup.ps1`

## Cursor AI + Godot (runs & scene/script changes)

Agent policy lives in **`godot-agent-godot-control.mdc`** (always applied): run Godot via CLI, edit project files, do not offload to the user unless they ask to drive the editor.

## Stale editor vs disk (\"Couldn't save scene\" / dependency warnings)

When Godot and Cursor both touch the same scripts, the editor can hold **stale buffers**. Saving scenes then triggers dependency / save failures.

**Repo fix (automatic):** this project includes **`addons/external_edit_sync`** (enabled in `project.godot`). On editor startup it ensures **Editor Settings → Text Editor → Behavior → Auto Reload Scripts on External Change** is **on**, so external saves reload into Godot without manual Project Reload.

**Still happens?** You have **unsaved edits in Godot’s script tabs** while Cursor also saved — resolve the conflict (save or revert in one place). Prefer **editing `.gd` in Cursor** and **leaving scenes** to Godot when possible to reduce `.tscn` churn.

**Human-readable checklist** (Output panel, scripts, missing files): **`guides/godot_save_scene_help.md`**.
